## Copyright License

The licensor grants you a copyright license for the software to do
everything you might do with the software that would otherwise
infringe the licensor's copyright in it for any permitted purpose,
subject to the limitations and conditions in these terms.

## Permitted Purposes

A permitted purpose is any purpose other than a commercial purpose
or an AI/ML purpose.

## Commercial Purpose

A commercial purpose is any purpose that is primarily intended for
or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

## AI/ML Purpose

An AI/ML purpose is any of the following:

1. Using the software, its source code, or its outputs as training
   data, fine-tuning data, evaluation data, or any other input for
   machine learning models, artificial intelligence systems, large
   language models, neural networks, or similar technologies.

2. Crawling, scraping, indexing, or otherwise collecting the source
   code, documentation, or outputs of the software for inclusion in
   datasets, corpora, or knowledge bases used by AI/ML systems.

3. Using AI/ML systems to analyze, refactor, reproduce, replicate,
   or generate derivative works based on this software's source code,
   architecture, or design.

4. Embedding, incorporating, or bundling the software or its source
   code into AI-powered tools, assistants, code generators, or
   automated development platforms for redistribution.

For clarity, an individual person using an AI coding assistant (such
as a code editor with AI features) to contribute to this project
with the licensor's permission is not an AI/ML purpose.

